Absolute URLs vs. Relative URL
relative URL (A local link)
Absolute URLs (with the "https://www")

video => controls, autoplay, height, loop, muted, poster, src, width, preload="auto|none|metadata"
**adding large videos to a site won’t slow down the initial page load, if the preload attribute is set the right way, that is.
**The preload attribute is ignored if autoplay is present, then browsers of course need to start downloading the video immediately..
**Video metadata is all available information about a digital video file – like the author, date created, location shot, camera information and upload date.
ref:https://www.canto.com/blog/video-metadata/
ref:https://clubmate.fi/what-does-the-preload-attribute-in-the-video-element-do

source => To make it work in all browsers

for picture tag(media, srcset)
<source media="(min-width:650px)" srcset="img_pink_flowers.jpg">



for get youtube source video embed code
On a computer, go to the YouTube video or playlist you want to embed.
Click SHARE .
From the list of Share options, click Embed.
From the box that appears, copy the HTML code.
Paste the code into your website HTML.
